It shouldn't be a secret that I LOVE books. But what if books were just another pretty face?
I mean, I know you WANT to read all the books, but there just isn't time. What if I told you there are books you can buy just for their covers and how gorgeous they are?
And that no one will judge you because they are that pretty?
Mind you, I have read all these books because I am that kind of nerd, but when I saw how insanely gorgeous they were, I bought them for the store because of their covers. Yes, I was that person.
You can be too! 
With gilt pages, embossed covers, and beautiful designs, you aren't going to feel guilty if you don't read them. (I may judge you, but...)
These beautiful books make the ideal gift. They are the perfect accessory for a guest room nightstand. Your guests will think you are literary AND have the most exquisite taste. Fake it until you make it, I say!
So go ahead and judge a book by its cover. You'll be glad you did.

#beautifulbooks #chilternclassics #booklover #booklovers #independentbookstore #smallbookstore #dickensonthestrand

This wasn't the post that I had planned for today. At 3 AM on Monday morning, we were robbed... again. 
If you are new around here, you may or may not know that three months ago we were burglarized by someone smashing through our window with a sledgehammer They made off with over $50K in gowns and pajamas. 
Well, they did it again. The police seem to think it's the same culprit. Here's the story that aired on the news to give you all the details. 
It's horrible. I won't try to sugarcoat it. We feel violated, and there's little to no hope that the stolen goods will be recovered. 
So many people have reached out asking what they can do to help. The honest answer is to shop. We have barely recovered from the first robbery, and this one just hit hard. I don't think that I've even processed it yet. 
As you are shopping this holiday season, we appreciate your business. Every sale is a vote of confidence in what we do as a team. We value YOU, our community, so much. 
Thank you for supporting us and encouraging us through these tough times. Your love and support do not go unnoticed. 
Thank you to @nataliehee for telling our story! 
Link in stories.

2022 is coming to a close, and I'm eager to welcome 2023! We've had one of the best and hardest years ever.
I've learned so much. I've always thought of myself as a patient person, but the buildout of our new boutique tested that notion. It's almost been 2 years since I first saw the space, and to see the transformation finally coming to a close (I won't say the end because I have so many more ideas) is a relief. 
We closed out the year with the installation of our long-awaited @graciestudio wallpaper by @okcwallpaper . It's been a LONG time coming, but so worth it. I walk through the room now and can't believe I'm lucky to call this place mine. I have lots planned to show you exactly how it came to be and what makes it so special, so for now, visit its handpainted goodness in person for yourself!
This year has taught us a lot about our process. We grew in revenue and our team. There were moments when I wasn't sure we would get it all done (spoiler alert, we did!). Because of our growth, we had more tight turnarounds than we ever anticipated, and we knew that to offer you the level of luxury you deserve, we needed to look at our process and improve it. 
Our new Design Consultation process is among many other systems we are implementing behind the scenes. If you are interested in having something made in the new year and have not yet scheduled your appointment, you'll want to read the BLOG about these changes. Don't worry! It's to make life better for everyone, especially you!
Thank you again for supporting us this year. The amount of love we received after (both) of the robberies was staggering. Knowing that we have a community that cares about us as much as we care about them is everything. 
Thank you for being here with us this year. I'm thrilled to see you in person in 2023 and to show you the new wallpaper!

As I look back at this past year, I see so much joy along with the hard and it feels about right.
4 posts that show the love we have for our clients.
2 posts that show the strength of our team and community.
3 posts that show my love for travel and experiencing the world.
@best.nine.app got this year pretty right.
Here’s to all of this (minus the robberies) in 2023!
In the words of the great Stephen Sondheim:

Things will come out right now
We can make it so
Someone is on your side
No one is alone

#bestnine #topnine #2022recap 
#hny #2023

I’ve never been into the whole resolution thing, but 5 years ago I discovered having a word for the year. Looking back, I can totally see how each word that I’ve chosen has powerfully shaped the course of each year. 
What you put out there comes back to you. The universe responds to the energy we put out there, so being intentional about how we want to show up in the next year is critical to our success.
Even if at the very least it’s just a tool to guide our mindset, words have power.
Do you choose a word for the year? What is it? I’d love to know!
#wordoftheyear #intentions #consistency #lawofattraction #newyear2023 #resolutions

When I tell you this was years in the making, I’m not kidding! 
We’ve had the idea for a magazine for at least three years. There were always ideas about what it would be and what it would look like, but the team didn’t have the bandwidth to make it a top priority. I even did a mockup of the cover and added it to my vision board. 
When Joey on my team came to me with his marketing plan for 2023, he had mocked up a catalog of our new items and best sellers that we could send to clients. I loved it but knew there was more there. Then, it hit me. I pulled up the cover of “Maison” that I had saved and told him to take his idea and expand it into a magazine. 
And expand, he did! Our first issue is 44 pages of design and fun, including an interview with Jennifer Gracie from @graciestudio I’m so proud of what we have accomplished. It was a group effort, and the magazine is truly beautiful. For now, it’s strictly digital. We’ve optimized it to view on a phone or tablet, but you can just as easily view it online. Each page links to more information or other articles we know you will love. 
Let us know how you enjoy this inaugural issue of “Maison!” I can’t wait to hear what you think!

This would have made a great Galentine’s Day post, but tonight I’m feeling the feels and missing my Paris friends. 
I was asked to speak at my son’s school yesterday morning and as I was going through photos to put together the presentation, I came across so many wonderful memories of my time living in France. The friendships that I formed and the memories that I made have stayed with me . There was something so incredibly special about that time that I will never be able to re-create. There’s a sadness to that, but there’s also a joy in looking back at photos from that time. 
The friends that I made during those formative years are still some of my best friends. I’m so looking forward to reuniting with many of them when I go back to Paris next month. It always feels like home. 
#Paris #Home #travel #fearless #tbt #throwbackthursday

Are you having any fun? Is that even a question when you’re in Paris?!
Day 2 had us all over the city.
We started off with the terrific “Gold” exhibit @museeyslparis followed by lunch and the always terrific @monsieur_bleu .
After lunch, we headed across the street to @palaisgallieramuseedelamode for the Big Bang show breaking down 1997 in fashion.
Dinner was delicious @chezcasimirparis . The Paris Brest was the bomb. 
The evening ended with my favorite Bar Hemingway @ritzparis with good friends.
Could ask for a better day in Paris!

#travel #paris #parisguis #yslmuseum #ritzparis #barhemingway

🎉 Reflecting on 2023 like... “Was that a year or a roller coaster?” 🎢 Grateful for the growth, but let’s be real, it was a workout for my sanity! 💪😅

From navigating inventory puzzles to team shuffles, we conquered it all. 🧩 Shoutout to our amazing clients for sticking with us through the chaos – you’re the real MVPs! 🌟

Every year, I pick a word to vibe with, and 2023 was all about “Consistency.” Spoiler alert: It was more like “Consistently Figuring Stuff Out.” 🤷‍♂️💡

As we bid farewell to the chaos, drumroll, please... 🥁 Introducing my word of the year for 2024: Effortless. Because who needs more hustle when you can have more flow? 🚀✨

Here’s to simplifying the complex, embracing creativity, and making it all look easy-peasy (even when it’s not). Let’s keep the energy up, and maybe check in later to see if I’m nailing this whole ‘effortless’ thing. 😂👊

When I moved to Houston 14 years ago, I would have never thought I would find my people. Well, I did, and we’ve been through it all. The highs and lows of business, kids, life… it’s been a ride. 
I’m so lucky to call this group my friends, but it’s hard to know that we probably won’t be able to take a picture like this for years. 
Heather and Shawn are off on a multi-year adventure to Uruguay.  It’s hard to picture not having them in our daily life. Our kids have grown up together and even go to school together. 
I’m so excited for them and their new adventures, but I selfishly wish I could keep them here. 
H-Town won’t be the same without them! I know I won’t be the same without them.
